summary: thank you, @danielhowell and @amazingphil, for being a constant in my life. no matter the changes and turmoils i faced, i could...
body:
thank you, @danielhowell and @amazingphil, for being a constant in my life. no matter the changes and turmoils i faced, i could always turn to you two for comfort and a sense of stability from my middle school years to today’s university graduation.

you taught me to rejoice in the weird, embrace the void, and have the courage to exist, and for that, i can never thank you enough. 🖤✌🏻

summary: People being upset at dan and phil both makes no sense and all the sense and it’d be cool if people would calm down because some...
question: People being upset at dan and phil both makes no sense and all the sense and it’d be cool if people would calm down because some people come here to get away from life stuff and dan’s dealing with life stuff probably and if people would chill out that’d be nice maybe
answer:
I just feel like people have no right to be mad at them tbh? Like they really don’t owe us anything?

“But we pay for their livelihood!”

We did. And if they don’t make content anymore then we aren’t really paying for anything. Also it’s up to you if you don’t want to buy/watch their stuff. Personally I haven’t bought anything from them since DAPGO came out. I don’t have a lot of money and I choose to spend what I do have elsewhere.

There are so many other creators busting their asses to make a living, why not support them? Some of them even become your friends.

It’s not like they did or have any horrible views. They aren’t suddenly evil. Maybe Phil’s overcompensating and maybe you’re tired of him and his constant sponning, but I bet you were one of those people the past few years saying he deserved just as much love as Dan.

Of course your opinions are allowed to change but like your negativity is affecting people, even if it’s validating other Negative Nancy’s out there.
